18:19.180 --> 18:22.120
Larry Niven is one of the best-selling authors in the field of science fiction.

18:22.120 --> 18:28.580
A fairly large portion of his work falls into the Known Space series, a group of stories and novels with a consistent chronology.

18:29.140 --> 18:30.980
Such a series is called a Future History.

18:31.740 --> 18:36.080
Niven believes there are some peculiar attractions a Future History has for a science fiction author.

18:36.840 --> 18:43.480
There had been Future Histories around, uh, Poole Anderson and, uh, Robert Heinlein.

18:45.560 --> 18:51.840
And I tell you, I guess we each evolved the idea somewhat independently.

18:52.140 --> 19:00.920
And the idea is that if you carved out a consistent, workable future, it seems a shame to waste it on one story.

19:02.260 --> 19:10.720
You put in the background because you want the, uh, you want the background of a story to seem bigger than it is.

19:10.720 --> 19:13.160
So there are things that are simply unexplained.

19:14.620 --> 19:19.640
And if you think of more to say on a given subject, why you go with it.

19:19.800 --> 19:26.320
And if you think of a story that fits into the background of a previous story and allows you to elaborate on that background,

19:26.820 --> 19:28.920
sometimes you fall in love with the background.

19:29.580 --> 19:32.040
And presently you've got a bunch of stories that link.

19:43.800 --> 19:47.700
Niven has also written some bestselling books that fall outside his known space series.

19:48.260 --> 19:54.680
Three of these, The Mote in God's Eye, Lucifer's Hammer, and Oath of Fieldty were written in collaboration with Jerry Purnell.

19:55.160 --> 19:57.200
We asked Niven how he and Purnell collaborate.

19:58.380 --> 20:02.000
Hard sometimes, but it always resolved.

20:02.720 --> 20:09.480
The question is who is more, who is most qualified to write a given scene that we have both decided needs writing.

20:10.060 --> 20:13.060
Before we start, we have the novel all laid out.

20:13.960 --> 20:17.080
We know what's going in virtually everywhere.

20:17.420 --> 20:19.280
And if we don't, it feels like we do.

20:20.220 --> 20:23.760
And if we find out we don't, we elaborate as we get to that section.

20:25.120 --> 20:28.620
Okay, the next question is who is qualified to write a given scene.

20:28.820 --> 20:29.800
Sometimes it's obvious.

20:30.740 --> 20:33.020
If we're dealing with a madman, he's mine.

20:33.680 --> 20:37.240
If we're dealing with military operations, it's Jerry's.

20:37.240 --> 20:39.560
Aliens are generally mine.

20:40.520 --> 20:42.760
Politics is generally Jerry's.

20:43.900 --> 20:46.560
Knowledge of history generally Jerry's.

20:47.000 --> 20:54.200
And a real evil son of a bitch, Jerry usually creates him and I usually run with him afterwards.

21:03.240 --> 21:06.340
Niven occasionally writes science fiction humor, rarity.

21:06.920 --> 21:08.760
He talks about his most successful piece of humor.

21:09.680 --> 21:18.360
I suppose I could name old man of steel woman of queen eggs, which has gotten me the most laughs.

21:18.360 --> 21:21.640
I suppose everybody seems to have read it.

21:21.760 --> 21:24.400
Those who haven't heard about it are cocktail parties.

21:25.660 --> 21:34.700
Niven's ready eye for humor can also be appreciated as he reveals that he's detected one of his own alien creations from Ringworld, the Pearson's puppeteer here on Earth.

21:35.740 --> 21:38.860
I have reason to suspect that there are puppeteers on Earth.

21:40.200 --> 21:41.380
Look at the characteristics.

21:42.360 --> 21:42.940
Forget the shape.

21:42.940 --> 21:47.640
They must be masters of biology that hide that peculiar three-legged two-headed shape.

21:48.140 --> 21:50.300
But consider their characteristics.

21:50.620 --> 21:51.420
They are cowards.

21:52.980 --> 21:55.560
That is, they want everything utterly safe.

21:56.360 --> 21:57.740
No corners on anything.

21:58.040 --> 22:00.820
Everything is soft surfaces around the puppeteer world.

22:01.700 --> 22:09.140
They don't even keep their world near a sun regarding it as a runaway fusion reactor, which of course it is.

22:10.740 --> 22:26.340
So, desperate regard for safety, they plus an urge to meddle in the lifestyles of other species, driving urge to meddle with practically no restraints attached.

22:27.060 --> 22:28.240
What does that remind you of?

22:28.560 --> 22:32.100
It seems nearly certain to me that Ralph Nader is a Pearson's puppeteer.

